definition.value: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid bearing an oxo group at the alpha carbon atom.
An aminopyrimidine that is pyrimidine in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 4, and 5 are replaced by methyl, amino, and hydroxymethyl substituents, respectively.
A sphingoid 1-phosphate that is the monophosphorylated derivative of  sphinganine.
A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by an (ethylsulfanyl)methyl group at position 2.
